  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The forthcoming publication, \"Virtual Innovation and Support Networks,\" by Peter Lang Verlag, is poised to contribute to the critical discourse surrounding digital collaboration and networks in innovation. An emphasis on commercial linkage suggests potential relevance to industry practices and implications for policy sustainability.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Virtual Innovation and Support Networks,\" set for release in 2024 by Peter Lang Verlag, represents a significant addition to the scholarly conversation on digital innovation. Given its strong commercial linkage, evidenced by positive associations with platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads, the book is likely to attract interest from both academic and non-academic audiences, emphasizing its potential application in real-world contexts.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Of particular note is the inferred strength of the work's relevance to sustainability and policy, reflected by its alignment with one of the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). This connection highlights the broader implications that virtual innovation can have on societal structures and sustainable practices, indicating the book's potential for influencing policy discussions.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of citations and digital discussion metrics at this time, the book's emergence can still be viewed as a proactive contribution to the knowledge landscape. It invites future academic uptake by addressing pertinent themes surrounding the interplay of technology and community engagement in support networks.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Furthermore, the book's visibility in the academic database, the Directory of Open Access Books (DOAB), showcases an acknowledgment of its scholarly value. Its presence there suggests a commitment to accessibility and dissemination of knowledge within the academic community, promoting further dialogue and inquiry in the field of virtual innovation.</p>",
